verses.text_plain: Though I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, and have not charity, I am become as sounding brass, or a tinkling cymbal.
verses.verse_html: 1Though I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, and have not charity, I am become as sounding brass, or a tinkling cymbal.

verses.text_plain: And though I have the gift of prophecy, and understand all mysteries, and all knowledge; and though I have all faith, so that I could remove mountains, and have not charity, I am nothing.
verses.verse_html: 2And though I have the gift of prophecy, and understand all mysteries, and all knowledge; and though I have all faith, so that I could remove mountains, and have not charity, I am nothing.

verses.text_plain: And though I bestow all my goods to feed the poor, and though I give my body to be burned, and have not charity, it profiteth me nothing.
verses.verse_html: 3And though I bestow all my goods to feed the poor, and though I give my body to be burned, and have not charity, it profiteth me nothing.

verses.text_plain: Charity suffereth long, and is kind; charity envieth not; charity vaunteth not itself, is not puffed up,
verses.verse_html: 4Charity suffereth long, and is kind; charity envieth not; charity vaunteth not itself, is not puffed up,

verses.text_plain: Doth not behave itself unseemly, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked, thinketh no evil;
verses.verse_html: 5Doth not behave itself unseemly, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked, thinketh no evil;

verses.text_plain: Rejoiceth not in iniquity, but rejoiceth in the truth;
verses.verse_html: 6Rejoiceth not in iniquity, but rejoiceth in the truth;

verses.text_plain: Beareth all things, believeth all things, hopeth all things, endureth all things.
verses.verse_html: 7Beareth all things, believeth all things, hopeth all things, endureth all things.

verses.text_plain: Charity never faileth: but whether there be prophecies, they shall fail; whether there be tongues, they shall cease; whether there be knowledge, it shall vanish away.
verses.verse_html: 8Charity never faileth: but whether there be prophecies, they shall fail; whether there be tongues, they shall cease; whether there be knowledge, it shall vanish away.

verses.text_plain: For we know in part, and we prophesy in part.
verses.verse_html: 9For we know in part, and we prophesy in part.

verses.text_plain: But when that which is perfect is come, then that which is in part shall be done away.
verses.verse_html: 10But when that which is perfect is come, then that which is in part shall be done away.

verses.text_plain: When I was a child, I spake as a child, I understood as a child, I thought as a child: but when I became a man, I put away childish things.
verses.verse_html: 11When I was a child, I spake as a child, I understood as a child, I thought as a child: but when I became a man, I put away childish things.

verses.text_plain: For now we see through a glass, darkly; but then face to face: now I know in part; but then shall I know even as also I am known.
verses.verse_html: 12For now we see through a glass, darkly; but then face to face: now I know in part; but then shall I know even as also I am known.

verses.text_plain: And now abideth faith, hope, charity, these three; but the greatest of these is charity.
verses.verse_html: 13And now abideth faith, hope, charity, these three; but the greatest of these is charity.
